1
00:00:05,670 --> 00:00:09,314
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur is saying,
“Do not join in a kīrtan

2
00:00:09,314 --> 00:00:11,158
not performed 
by a pure devotee.”

3
00:00:11,288 --> 00:00:13,231
[Counterfeit Sound]

4
00:00:13,231 --> 00:00:17,706
Like there are these so-called kīrtans
on the Internet, or singers, performers,

5
00:00:17,706 --> 00:00:24,768
and sometimes they have names
that sound like devotee names,

6
00:00:24,768 --> 00:00:28,274
but they’re not actually Vaiṣṇavas.

7
00:00:28,274 --> 00:00:33,350
So we’re told not to join
into that kīrtan, not to hear.

8
00:00:33,350 --> 00:00:36,887
avaiṣṇava-mukhodgīrṇaṁ 
pūtaṁ hari-kathāmṛtam

9
00:00:36,887 --> 00:00:41,527
śravaṇaṁ naiva kartavyaṁ 
sarpochchhiṣṭaṁ yathā payaḥ
[Padma Purāṇa]

10
00:00:41,527 --> 00:00:45,768
Sanātan Goswāmī is very heavy about it
saying, “Do not hear it!”

11
00:00:45,768 --> 00:00:48,487
We think, “No, but I thought hearing 
the tava kathāmṛtam,

12
00:00:48,487 --> 00:00:51,017
hearing about Kṛṣṇa,
hearing the name of Kṛṣṇa,

13
00:00:51,017 --> 00:00:53,718
this is what
will liberate everyone;

14
00:00:53,718 --> 00:00:56,643
Mahāprabhu descended to give
the Hari-nam to everyone …

15
00:00:56,643 --> 00:00:58,763
Now you’re saying, 
‘Not to hear!”’

16
00:00:58,763 --> 00:01:02,477
Yes, because now
it comes down to quality,

17
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,490
what is the quality 
of Kṛṣṇa-nam.

18
00:01:05,490 --> 00:01:08,347
In one place 
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur says that

19
00:01:08,347 --> 00:01:11,672
māyāvādīs also chant 
the name of Kṛṣṇa.

20
00:01:11,672 --> 00:01:13,569
He said, “But when they take
the name of Kṛṣṇa,

21
00:01:13,569 --> 00:01:17,661
it’s like a thunderbolt
hitting the holy body of Kṛṣṇa.”

